  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Danish Emergency Relief Fund (DERF) is a funding mechanism established in 2017 by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs. 

The objective of DERF is to prevent the loss of life and escalation of suffering among people affected by acute humanitarian crises. This is done by establishing a mechanism that is rapid, effective, flexible, and relevant. The DERF enables Danish civil society organisations and their partners to respond to acute humanitarian crises and to reach affected populations by responding to their needs. 

To learn more: https://www.cisu.dk/derf</narrative>
  </description>
